This project is an AI-based job assistant that helps users find suitable jobs by analyzing their resume.
It extracts important features like skills and compares them with job descriptions to give a match score.
Based on the extracted skills, it also suggests relevant jobs and internships from online platforms.
The project is built using HTML, CSS, JavaScript for frontend and Python Flask for backend processing.
It is deployed online using Railway with Gunicorn, making the application accessible through a public URL.


1️⃣ Python vs Flask
Python:
A programming language.
Can write anything: scripts, data processing, AI, web apps.
Flask:
A Python framework for building web applications.
Makes Python capable of handling web requests (like login forms, file uploads, showing web pages).
Without Flask (or another framework), Python alone cannot serve a website.
